line_1: And steep'd them softly in a Statesman's Skull.
line_2: From thence Debates and long Harangues to cull,

line_1: What the black Mists afflict the aking Skull,
line_2: The Spirits tremble and the Heart be dull:

line_1: There hardly was room left to thrust in your skull.
line_2: To see such a contest the house was so full
